abstract: Bernie Sanders' Democratic presidential rivals warn that nominating the self-described democratic socialist will ensure President Donald Trump's re-election, but a growing number of the party's voters see the senator as their best chance of winning in November.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' Democratic presidential rivals warn that nominating the self-described democratic socialist will ensure President Donald Trump's re-election, but a growing number of the party's voters see the senator as their best chance of winnin...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Bernie Sanders' Democratic presidential rivals warn that nominating the self-described democratic socialist will ensure President Donald Trump's re-election, but a growing number of the party's voters see the senator as their best chance of winning in November.
headline_main: Can Sanders Beat Trump? A Growing Number of Democratic Voters Say Yes
headline_print_headline: Can Sanders Beat Trump? A Growing Number of Democratic Voters Say Yes

abstract: Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under attack from his rivals on Tuesday as seven candidates competing to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November debated in Charleston, South Carolina.
snippet: Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under attack from his rivals on Tuesday as seven candidates competing to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November debated in Charleston, South Carolina.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under attack from his rivals on Tuesday as seven candidates competing to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November debated in Charleston, South Carolina.
headline_main: 'Chaos ... Coming Our Way'-Top Quotes From the Democratic Presidential Debate
headline_print_headline: 'Chaos ... Coming Our Way'-Top Quotes From the Democratic Presidential Debate

abstract: At a raucous debate, Bernie Sanders was the target, but who really got hurt?

abstract: The stakes could not have been higher at the Democratic presidential debate on Tuesday, with the South Carolina primary and Super Tuesday contests looming in the week ahead.
snippet: The stakes could not have been higher at the Democratic presidential debate on Tuesday, with the South Carolina primary and Super Tuesday contests looming in the week ahead.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The stakes could not have been higher at the Democratic presidential debate on Tuesday, with the South Carolina primary and Super Tuesday contests looming in the week ahead.
headline_main: Raucous Democratic Debate Yields No Clear Challenger to Sanders
headline_print_headline: Raucous Democratic Debate Yields No Clear Challenger to Sanders

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates unleashed withering attacks on Bernie Sanders in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, assailing his ambitious economic agenda and warning his nomination would be a "catastrophe" that would cost Democrats the White House and control of Congress.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates unleashed withering attacks on Bernie Sanders in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, assailing his ambitious economic agenda and warning his nomination would be a "catastrophe" that would cost Democ...
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic presidential candidates unleashed withering attacks on Bernie Sanders in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, assailing his ambitious economic agenda and warning his nomination would be a "catastrophe" that would cost Democrats the White House and control of Congress.
headline_main: At Rowdy Debate, Democratic Rivals Warn Sanders Nomination Would Be 'Catastrophe'
headline_print_headline: At Rowdy Debate, Democratic Rivals Warn Sanders Nomination Would Be 'Catastrophe'

abstract: Eyeing a South Carolina victory to rescue his presidential ambitions, Joe Biden claimed one of the state's most coveted endorsements on Wednesday as Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders marched past the blistering assault from his rivals on the debate stage the night before.
snippet: Eyeing a South Carolina victory to rescue his presidential ambitions, Joe Biden claimed one of the state's most coveted endorsements on Wednesday as Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders marched past the blistering assault from his rivals on the ...
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Eyeing a South Carolina victory to rescue his presidential ambitions, Joe Biden claimed one of the state's most coveted endorsements on Wednesday as Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders marched past the blistering assault from his rivals on the debate stage the night before.
headline_main: Biden Claims Momentum as Sanders Marches Past Debate Fray
headline_print_headline: Biden Claims Momentum as Sanders Marches Past Debate Fray

abstract: With 17 contests at stake over the next week, the night took on a frenetic pace. Sanders faced the most scrutiny yet, Warren continued to bite into her rivals and Buttigieg and Klobuchar faded.
snippet: With 17 contests at stake over the next week, the night took on a frenetic pace. Sanders faced the most scrutiny yet, Warren continued to bite into her rivals and Buttigieg and Klobuchar faded.
lead_paragraph: From the opening bell, the Democratic candidates sparred with the desperation of the looming deadline. Sixteen states and territories will vote in the next week and everyone has little time to slow the building momentum of Senator Bernie Sanders, who leads in the early delegate chase and has won the most votes in each of the first three states.

abstract: The democratic socialist found himself in the center — of the stage and the squabbling.
snippet: The democratic socialist found himself in the center — of the stage and the squabbling.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders was pointing — to the left, to the right, at himself, at the sky — in one moment coming under such ubiquitous duress that he extended both hands outward, as if pushing to the front of a crowd, to swat back stage-wide accusations of fuzzy math.
